stylometry:
Transportation models deal only with:
	Nodes - or the locations on a network (cities, computers, etc.)
	Arcs - the pathways between nodes (distanc between cities, cables between computers, etc.)
	Flows - the amount that travels (size of shipment, amount of data sent, etc.)

Trans-shipment models deal with these as well but with one difference. These models deal in warehouses, points in travel where a shipment will come in to a building, but also leave quickly rather than being put into inventory. That way there is not as much inventory being held at these locations, but instead allow the incoming shipments to be redistributed to new locations.
